node.text:
Sound on 🔊 Make the most of what’s left of grilling season by making our juiciest chicken ever—topped with fresh, homemade Chimichurri sauce. This herby, green sauce is an easy way to level up your favorite protein. 

TIPS
→ Use chicken breast with skin on to lock all of the flavors.
→ Hand-chop your herbs to avoid creating a watery sauce.
→ The fresher the herbs, the greener the sauce.

→ A marble board helps keep dough cold.

Say hello to summer brunch with this super delicious, homemade Bloody Mary mix. Use it to set up a fun self-serve bar. It gets guests excited and takes bartending off your plate. 

TIPS
→ Garnish with classic mix-ins like Tabasco & celery and rim your glasses with lemon juice & tajín. 
→ Use the ripest and darkest tomatoes you can find at the peak of the season, as they will have the most flavor.
→ Fresh tomato juice will be much lighter in color than store-bought mixes, many of which contain other ingredients to intensify the red.
→ Refrigerate beforehand to let the flavors develop.

Get the recipe & learn more at: bit.ly/3hpUNR2. Stay tuned for more quick how-tos and seasonal recipes.

Sound on 🔊 It’s officially grilling season. As these summertime fruits cook, their natural sugars caramelize and provide a complex flavor to snack on their own or use in our fave three recipes:
-Grilled Peaches with Prosciutto
-Grilled Pineapple Salsa
-Watermelon, Feta and Basil Salad

TIPS:
→ Fruit should be ripe, but not overly ripe so it can stand up to the heat of the grill. 
→ Lightly brush fruit with a neutral oil, such as canola or grapeseed.
→ Sear quickly, just enough to see grill marks.

Sound on 🔊 Take your summer baking outdoors with this strawberry & blackberry cobbler recipe that bakes on the grill in a cast iron skillet. 😮 This picture-perfect dessert is easier than you think to make and will please everyone at the cookout. Just top with vanilla ice cream for a sweet welcome to summer.

PRO TIPS:
→ Use a strawberry huller to quickly remove cores.
→ Cut strawberries in half to hold their shape.
→ Taste berries and adjust amount of sugar based on their sweetness (or tartness!).
→ To check if it’s baked well on the grill, look for the biscuits to be golden brown & the fruit to be bubbly hot.

Get the recipe & learn more at: bit.ly/3wUsLlC. Stay tuned for more quick how-tos and seasonal recipes.

Designing a small outdoor space? Take colorful interior designer @dabito’s styling advice: 💛
→ “For small spaces, I like round pieces, like tables or ottomans, because they allow flow. Don’t be afraid to maximize every inch of the space by filling it up. People are always nervous about filling up small spaces because they’re scared it’ll feel cramped, but that’s the opposite—the more you add, the more cozy it becomes. Find pieces that can do triple duty that offer storage, seating and table. Foldable tables and chairs are also great for small spaces.
